reviews.text: Liked it. Nice place

One of the best regional museums in Southern Bohemia, and not crowded with the hordes of tourists you see on all other hotspots of Krumlov. Take 2-3 hours of time and enjoy!
Czech language skills are for sure benefits your experience, not all descriptions are translated.
A bit hot and missing some English but it was an interesting museum.
If you are interested in Czech history in general,  and the history of this town,  go and spend an hour or so.
Friendly interesting museum.

Awesome attraction, a bit scary at first place, though a valuable insight into miners' working environment and overall conditions. Can be also guided in English (on request). Otherwise go with English speaking local to get the best out of it.
Was amazing! The only reason for loss of star was that it felt quite rushed, after all the effort donning the gear we were only inside for 40 minutes. For €4 I would do it again!

Nice tour to see how it was till 2003 when the mine closed (started in 1975). Only guided tours. Guide language in Czech. But translations on paper available. Don't worry if you forgot your socks... They have replacement sleeves available. Luckely for us 😉.

The mine was an interesting experience taking a small train into a mountain on a hot day and then being in a cave that was freezing. I really enjoyed the break from the heat. The mine was cool seeing graphite on the walls. In some areas you could see and touch veins of graphite.
Interesting tour which the guide also translated in English for us. Not a lot of details about life in the mine etc. but anyway a nice visit including a trip in a small mine train.

Very warm and friendly services. Food was great too! The vibe was easy going and perfect (we sat outdoor). We had their recommended set (garlic soup, pork knee, and honey cake).

We were told by others that this restaurant requires advanced reservation and we went at the time early for dinner and luckily we got the table straightaway. And sure enough, about half an hour later, the customers kept pouring in. 

Would recommend advanced reservation.
Without making reservations, we were given a table very quickly and the waitress was so friendly and helpful. Food was excellent and so was the coffee. Great service.

Great open fire grill restaurant. Very busy, you need much luck to get a table without the reservation.
We were lucky to get the table in front of the fire. The food was great!
Food Not delicious. The waitress asked for 10% tip which was not nice.  I strongly don't recommend.
Food was great. If you come across chinese tourist sound might disturbe you because it is a small place. It has a dark athmosphere. And when you get out you smell like roasted beef.
Service was good; nice waiter, but the food was not so good.
Very nice place to eat! Great service a variety of food! Great location! I highly recommend this place!
Fried pork chop tastes good enough for me, cozy place to have a meal!

Kind of surprised reading others people reviews to this place. Our experience was totally different. The lady that attend is was incredibly friendly and welcoming. I tried the pork on mushroom sauce and it was very nice. Service was a bit slow but we not mind as we really enjoyed our food.
Nice place. Food was ok. Service is bad and unfriendly.

We walked into this place because of a recommendation from a friend. I wasn't planning on writing a review but after the first bite I knew that I had share the experience. It took me until I ate half the pizza to be able to take the picture and before I knew it the whole pizza was gone. The service was amazing. I told the server to surprise me with a random pizza and her choice was just what I needed. If you're reading this review then you're looking for a place to eat pizza and I can assure you, that you won't be let down with Nonna Gina.

Pizza was fine (not great but fine). We took two soups: one with vegetables (they simply unfronzened them and put in the broth) and one with chickpeas (from the can). The soups we took were very bad, in Italy for sure you cannot find something like that...in Czech Rep neither.
Great service and price, love the pizza

Nice quiant little Italian spot not far from the Castle walk. Great beer/wine options. Pizza was muy authentico! 

Perfect long lunch after a morning of walking.
One of the best Italian places I have ever been to! God service and cozy atmosphere!
Superb chocolate. I love hot chocolate shot also.

If you are a chocolate lover, u should pay a visit here. The lady is very helpful and patient to explain to me which chocolate to choose according what you love. Chocolate drink is a must if u love chocolate but must drink it when it's still hot.
Amazing chocolate shop. Delicious hot chocolate shots!
Sve je ljepo isplati se posjetiti
服務態度很差會趕人，巧克力選擇多會不知道怎麼選擇，對於個人口味來說算甜，擺飾好看但包裝不雅致。
One of the approximately 1300 Jewish cemeteries in Hungary. The place is well maintaned, easy to find, it is open as a rule, except Saturdays.
There's a guy living there and will let you in just have to ring the bell, in addition he helped us get a taxi to get back  it's a must visit if your in the area
Beautiful old cemetery. Only by appointment!

The botanic gardens are beautiful! Very well kept. I enjoyed the greenhouses too, such a variety of lovely plants. I can tell a lot of care goes in to looking after them. I wish there were some animals in the tropical house. Nice for an afternoon stroll.

Really blissful ..you can have a good walk here.
of course when the weather is good.. 
You can see a wide variety of flowers.. well maintained.

The Ulster museum at one corner for the park is definitely worth a visit...& there is no entry fee.
Wonderful gardens, and amazing hot houses. Beautifully set out.  And with the Ulster Museum on the grounds. Amazing.  All lovers of plant life, and Creation in general will enjoy time spent here.

Had a great day walking around the craft fair. Seen many spectacular flowers, massive vegetables and lots of stalls selling home made produces. The fudge was fantastic.

Found the Belfast ukelele jam group playing in a marquee. Wow great music.

Pleasant in the early Spring. The flowerbeds are full of vibrant colour. The hothouses are rich with blooms and scents. The lawns have not yet shaken off their winter rough and are damp, but not for long. The renovated tropical ravine is superb and the museum is nearby if it rains or you need a snack. If it's sunny, go and look at the herbacious borders; sit and listen to the bees at work.
I am studying here nd learning........

Do not miss the Museum of Contemporary Art in Bangkok! Not only is it a wonderful museum it is also a stunning piece of modern architecture. You'll need all day and then some more, a dream for any art buff there's five floors of spectacular exhibits. On the ground floor there's a restaurant, garden and an interactive experience. Take the family.  I loved it and next time I'm in Bangkok I'll be heading back for another look.👍🌟🌟🌟🌟🌟

The Museum of Contemporary Art is from 2012. It is a private museum housed in a large building. 

There is no double pricing. Same price for a Thai and a foreigner. If you  are more than 60, you can enter for free. Not only Thais, but also foreigners. The price for a regular ticket is TB 250.

Obviously, most of the items on display in this museum are from Thailand, but on the fifth floor there is an interesting collection of foreign items.

Next to all items on display is a label with information in Thai and in English. 

You are allowed to use a camera inside the museum, but you cannot use a flash. There is one exception: you are not allowed to take pictures inside the special Robert Green collection on the fifth floor.

There is a coffee shop on the ground floor. There is a car park in the basement. 

The staff are friendly and helpful.

If you are interested in contemporary art, this place is definitely worth a visit.

Oh....
This is an ....hard to say.
They declare that this is a contemporary museum but this museum does not explore the comprehensive contemporary art all over the world because it’s simply this is a private museum owned by one business man.the collection is rely on his taste.of course this museum is playing a key role for collecting national artists of Thailand but mainly the collection is reflected on his preference.
I really love this spot because I can enjoy the most sophisticated art works in Bangkok.
I’ll come back here again.

Great museum. 
Beautiful building. Lots of great surrealism and some traditional Thai art. 
Definitely worth going although it's hard to get to, since the nearby train is not operational yet. Try to make sure your cab driver knows the place. Took us some time to get there but was worth it 👍👍

Surprisingly beautiful (and modern) structure that houses mostly modern and some traditional art. Peacefully quiet—not many locals seem aware it exists. The art is fascinating—a modern reinterpreting traditional Thai aesthetic forms. Lovely reprieve from the hot chaos of the city.
Very good food and service
The best affordable place in Las Mercedes
Excelent place to eat Italian food
The best pizza in Mercedes neighborhood.
good for pizzas
The place is very disappointing. The waiters are in a rush, forcing you to order fast even that you haven't seen the menu and the staff is making you feel unpleasant!
Food was amazing. The service was awesome. I reccomend you visit, you wont regret it.

Ordered goulash, spiced pork sausage, and pork roast for the table. Meals were very nice. Nothing to write home about, but nothing at all to fault. Service was OK, waiter very pleasant, wait time was a bit delayed given total number of patrons.

I am giving one star, because there is no option for less!!!! 
The waiters were rushed, ordering behalf our name, and telling us things like “ Cam-on we are waiting 100 people what do you want” or “is thus the first time in a restaurant ?” literally less than a minute after they gave us the menu!! 
I let that pass by because of the place reputation, but the food was nothing special, way too salty and again during the time we ate the waiters were in a rush! This is definitely not a nice place ti eat!!!
I have enjoyed stay there. Taste food, fast staff, reasonable price. Recommend
Superb food. Very good service.
Excellent Indian food. The tikka masala and naan bread are great.
Very good india food!!
Usually very good but lately not no good and children’s menu is awful.
Food was tasty. But they charged us an extra 25% mva tax on top of menu price which we have since found out is not common practice.
Delicious, authentic Vietnamese at affordable prices. Veggie options available. Fast, friendly service.
vietnamese food, yeah, super yummy. Stopped in on a Tuesday. Looking forward to a return trip. It has a good feel to it.
Amazing authentic food, great service. Can go wrong with an Austin classic!

This is a nice place in a strip mall.  I came later in the day for lunch and was surprised how busy they were.  This is. Good sign of how the food is.  The service was quick and friendly.  The food didn't take long to make and tasted good.  The menu is large with lots of options including vegetarian, so there is something for even the picky eaters.
Food was terrible. Service was rude. And they started cleaning while we were there, which emitted a terrible smell.
Expensive and limited parking space.

One of the best Pizza Huts in the area. First folks in so the buffet wasn’t completely out yet. Though the food that was, was absolutely delicious & hot. Staff was friendly & on top of things. Restaurant was pretty clean & well organized.
SO so ummy...and I love supporting young readers -- thanks, Hut! ...did I mention how very yummy the pizza was? Seriously. Good pizza 🥰
Love their pizza! It's the best anywhere. The service at this one is amazing, too!
Food was good and so was the service. Waitress was great also!
Pizza hut has been always the best pizza and love the salads and sauces. Great services as well.

Mid segment India n restaurant near to lake area. For Indians it has good options and worth. Price is moderate. I tried this during my  many visits. People are good. Lot of Indians and Pakistanis can been seen here. Places location is great. Need to improve ambience and overall service, quality and taste standards. Wash rooms need refurbishement.

it was terrible. servers are arrogant. they did not give me even a cup of water. whenever i asked them several times, they just stand on chairs and kept their eyes on their phone. it was lunch time on weekdays. they didn't not busy. there was 3 servers and only 3 groups of customers. is it an excessive demand? when he gave me a cup of water, he slammed that. the water splashed on table. but he just went out without any apology for his rudeness.
CLOSED DOWN FOR BUSINESS!
It's closed Permanently. Anyone looking for Indian food, please find another place
food is ok...not completely indian taste....Saturday buffet is goo choice
The administrator lady is very rude. She goes to kitchen without uniform. We tried to ask her why but the answer was: It is not your bussiness.The vodka quality is very bad (we had Beluga on friday).
Been there many times during my 4-month stay in Almaty.  Nice place but bit expensive in terms of Almaty.
Legendary place and good food
Great music and dancing

Great look and atmosphere
Discovered to late but definitely coming back

The museum has a good collection of medieval and Baroque art, though it is not presented in a way that makes it easy to follow or appreciate unless you're an expert. The fantastic Roman collection is still mostly in storage, though a small part has finally been returned to the Steinhalle (again the presentation is poor with little information and many objects hard to view).
Bit old fashion. English exist but not enough
Great Experience , nice pieces of art , lightening on paintings was perfect .

Magnificent collection organized by historical period and theme. I don't have a basis of comparison against other European galleries, but the baroque section was unlike anything I've seen at many major US city museums. Well worth the trip.
It was good for people who likes the history. Lots of paintings, statues. They offer route guide map and there are cloak rooms also.

Didn't visit the museum but the bar next to it. Can recommend: Very tasty spritzers and tasty beers. Atmosphere is great and staff was friendly. Only had to wait a bit long before they come take your order.
The Kunsthaus Graz, Grazer Kunsthaus is a museum of contemporary art built in 2003. I did not visit it, but the shape of this building immediately caught my eye because of its originality.
Architecturally, the Kunsthaus is a thing of beauty - a work of art. Inside is equally impressive. The exhibitions are nicely curated. 'Camera Austria' is currently displayed.
The breakfast was very good. The place deserves visiting.
good food , located near centre

No place around does the volume of meals as China Garden. It's a constant stop for Chinese tour buses on the weekend. Their dim sum is solid, but it's convenient if you're in DC or Arlington to get here compared to Falls Church or Silver Spring. The lady that runs the place can be a tad truculent, but she gives the place atmosphere.

Always feel free to reach out to me on Twitter @joerazz
Good Dim Sum food cart. It can get very busy during weekends due to tourist buses.  Excellent quality for Chinese party food. Unfortunately, they closed down in July 2017 and moved to Maryland.

Dim sum on a Saturday noon was surprisingly not busy.  The dumplings we're good, not great.  The roast duck was amazing, huge, fatty and full of flavor.  The ginger scallion lobster was also ok.  Service was very attentive.  Validated parking in the basement.

I used to be a motorcoach operator and brought many Asian Tour groups to this restaurant.
The food was always delicious. I was last at this restaurant in 2008.
If Asians eat at an Asian food establishment, the food has to be good. The food tastes just like quality restaurants in Chinatown, NYC

Pretty mediocre, but that might have been my bad for showing up right at the end of dim sum service. I got served cold squid, which luckily they replaced, and dumplings that had the stale texture of having been sitting out for hours. Would have been better if they had just told me no more dim sum.
I ordered a mild meal. Although I don’t like Spicy food, I do like my food flavorful. I felt that the mild dish I ordered was pretty bland, and could have had more flavor.

The food was pretty good, not the best indian I've had but good. Pretty good selection, not huge. Service was pretty good. The restaurant itself I found to be really cold and pretty small. Prices are very good, I think they are really fair. Overall good but I'm not dying to go back.
Absolutely wonderful place, fantastic options and delicious flavors. I wish I could go through the whole vegetarian menu - I haven't tried anything I haven't loved. Try the Masala tea!
The best Indian food in Iowa City, the Chicken Tikka Masala is the best. A great buffet selection with a lot of delicious Indian food.

This used to be our favorite place in IC. But it seems to have changed ownership or something over the course of the year. Each time we’ve gotten it the last few months, it has been disappointing in multiple ways. We kept trying it again because we’d loved it so much and were hoping it would get better again. But tonight was the last straw. Food was again very sub par and bad service. No more Masala for us and I don’t give it up lightly.
Nice Asian CH chain.  Good food, clean. Good service
Very good food and kind service

Simple, this place never fails to deliver and its great to be able to Swing backwards and forwards in your seat as you eat - Try it!! Its like being a child at a park! Beijing nights (Sweet and Sour Chicken) and rice is to die for and also their Pad Thai and fried rice. They also did like a Fried Chicken and fries which was like a KFC ,but obviously not KFC, but tasted better! :-D

I ordered online take away and when my husband got there they told us no order has been placed. Even though I received a confirmation. He was then quite left alone and had to ask a few times before they handled the matter.  Eventually, after 45min waiting, he finally got the food and still had to make his way home. I hoped at least the food was worth the waiting and the hastle, but the Vietnamese food was not authentic, you could smell that it was just beef-cube, and the noodles were still hard. I had to cook them again until they were edible... what if I were somewhere out?? what a pitty... would not order again.

This is our first visit since their upgrade. Great new menus, including the menu from their sister restaurant chain, Negishi and a drink menu with clever non-alcoholic options. We are certain to make this a regular haunt.

The staff are very nice, fast service, well curated menus: All would be perfect except for one thing. This may not bother some people, but it did concern me. If you need to use silverware, you have to take it out of a utensil bucket on the table. The spoons and forks are facing business end up. This means that when somebody pulls one out, the utensils next to them are being touched as well. Unless you just use chopsticks or order a large soup that comes with a spoon, you may be putting your mouth where a stranger put their hand :-(

Only some people would be bothered by this, but I really think they need to change how silverware is provisioned.

Other than that, the reinvented Nooch @ Barfi is a hard place to beat for Asian food in Basel.

Not as good as it used to be 4 years ago. I was looking forward to coming back and trying it again. I thought maybe it was just me but after reading other comments I know its not just me. Flavor is gone, mediocre food. Very little meat in my regular burrito which for me is just fine but there was also even less green chili. Great friendly service though.

My fiance and Father in law have been going here for years. Today was my first time and I loved it.
I ordered Huevos Rancheros with red Chile. Yummy yummy.
It was a trip for us but well worth it. I recommend adding this location to your "must stop" places.

These are the best new Mexican burritos around. You can't go wrong here. Try one of the meat or bean before going for the giant burrito thing. The giant one is good but you need to try the regular burritos to really know how good they are.
I think Albuquerque was built around this place. It has been here as long as I can remember. It serves a local version of Mexican fast food, which has always tasted great.
The food is good and the price is also good the service is quick  the location is not the best. It is if you work or live on military base. Even if you live in the hood.

Beautiful church! Was lucky enough to make it for a baroque organ show when I was there. (The sign said they have this on Thursday and Friday's at around 5). The musician invited us upstairs to get a close look at the pipe organ and he explained how it works. He also played some beautiful pieces on it!!! What a lovely experience! The show was free, but leaving a donation allows them to maintain the pipe organ.

Conveniently placed close to Alexander Platz, it is a great option to go in and collect your thoughts or light a candle for someone you love. Intrigued by the drawing at the entrance, which seems to depict a fun extraterrestrial party. Very X-Files.
Oldest church in Berlin, located near Alexanderplatz. Very beautiful inside. You can find here several interesting paintings. Absolutely recommend to visit this calm place.

Beautuful medival church in the heart of Berlin city Center, right next to alexanderplatz and fernseheturm. One of the oldest churches in Berlin. Inside the church you can find breathtaking baroque organs where famous musicians used to take their first organ classes, as well as famous fresco painting - the dance of death.

I’m not a Christian. 

But I prayed and the main reason why I prayed was the air. 

The air makes me think too deep. 

It’s free to go into the church. 

Also the tower is not that far from here.
Best
Mooi historisch pand aan de markt. Rondleidingen door het pand worden gegeven door Kring Vrienden van 's-Hertogenbosch.  Te boeken via dagjedenbosch.com. Een aanrader.
Beetje ouderwets.

In dit pand is onder andere de Ombudsman van de gemeente 's-Hertogenbosch gevestigd.
Deze Ombudsman is vaak de laatste strohalm die mensen hebben.
Echter is deze commissie niet van fouten verschoond, fouten die zij zelf toegegeven hebben.

Toch weerhouden die fouten hen er niet van om 'over lijken te gaan' en medewerkers van de gemeente die hun boekje te buiten gaan een handje boven het hoofd te blijven houden ! 

Wat in een onprofessionele, bijna corrupte en incompetente organisatie resulteert.
Men zal zich hier uiteraard 'niet in herkennen' maar dat is altijd het standaard rookgordijn dat snel opgetrokken wordt om zaken binnenkamers te houden.

For me the Kornhauskeller is one of the best restaurants in town. It's not the cheapest place for sure, but the food is very delicious and the atmosphere down in this amazing building is also very impressive! All together is absolutely worth a visit for everyone who likes great food and atmosphere and ready to pay the little extra for it.

Food good, great wine, but beware that you do pay a premium for the amazing location. Service was not up to standard of the prices, but very friendly. All in all, worth a visit just to dine in the amazing atmosphere of the high ceiling cellar.
Stopped here for drinks. It was tasty and the place had a really cool vibe. If I was in Bern I'd stop back here to take a chance at dinner. Really cool place.

Well worth a stop at the Gallery Bar for a drink, even if just for a beer, but recommend getting a cocktail. Google said it was closed on Monday, but it was open on the night that I went. You will go down a flight of stairs to get to the bar and then it is a second flight down to the restaurant.

A fantastically elegant location in the historic Kornhauskelker (grain storage cellar) situated on the heart of Bern. 
The place reeks of class and elegance. The staff are attentive but not obtrusive. Dimly lit but not too dim that you can't admire the wonderful murals adorning the walls and ceiling.
A great place for a special occasion.
The only church building in the city probably in the gothic style. I was pleasantly surprised to see it as I’m not a big fan of Eastern Orthodox architecture. This is good example of western culture.
Magnificent place, I am not catholic, but the building is beautiful
peacefull  place
The church is still under reconstruction. Fortunately, the worker let us go inside, although it is rarely available for visiting. Eerie atmosphere of neglected church, which is pretty cool!

Remnants of the main synagogue of Barcelona. Do not expect an actual synagogue, the Jewish community was forcefully converted in 1391, and it's main sites thoroughly destroyed. 
What remains of Jewish memory in Barcelona is scattered, and easy to overlook.
The hidden gem here are the guided visits the synagogue provides in Spanish, English, Hebrew, etc. They will help you to understand jewish life in medieval Barcelona.
They charge to go in so we didn't get past the front room. Looks cool though.
Worth a visit, €3.50 donation to enter. Quite small but full of fantastic history and staff give short speech on the jewish history and how it links in with Barcelona.

I had the pleasure to photograph a beautiful intimate wedding in the old Synagogue. I loved the atmosphere, the staff was very friendly, all prepared till a small little details for a perfect celebration.

We was not able to find the place on our first visit to Barcelona. It was around midnight in the middle of October - very common time for Barcelona to be out and explore place around. We wanted to find the Ancient Synagogue to be able to come here again at the day time. Interesting to say, at we were not alone, there was another couple trying to find the place - no luck. We returned next year at the day time,  we did it! It was worth the time and money to know the background of the Call carrer (Jewish community location in Barcelona).
Situated in the heart of city.Awesome place to hangout with friends. Friends can sit together for long time . Burgers are awesome in taste. All food items are good in taste.
Love to come here, after my coaching classes. It is very nice place for sitting with friends
Well !!!! Who doesn’t know abt Mcdonald 😄❤️ and i think 90% foodies will prefer to take a quick hunger break here. I request those 10% to fill the gap sooner the better 🔥 🔥🔥

It is situated in the Atlantis mall Civil lines......Prayagraj...... 
You all are well aware of the fact that it is a place mostly crowded.... it promotes self service.... the menu is being displayed on the screen above counters.... very limited items are there in this mcD Allahabad...  but it will be freshly prepared and served hot.... drinking water is available for free but one have to ask for it..... its affordable...... one cannot have a cosy atmosphere or a silent atmosphere since its generally over crowded....

I recommend you to taste ice creams...

I would prefer KFC for burgers. But if u want something lite than you ho for it.
The place is always crowded. Try the mcflurry and allu ticki
